description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Community Senior Practitioner (Registered Mental Health Nurse, Social Worker) to join the Scarborough integrated Community Mental Health Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit an enthusiastic, motivated and experienced clinician to deliver a care co-ordination role in the team. The successful candidates will be able to demonstrate strong clinical skills, daily team leadership and be a role model to others. At all times ensuring high quality care is delivered to individuals living with complex mental health needs over a variety of environments across the geographical area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be joining at a time of very busy and challenging times. They are expected to demonstrate a flexible and adaptable approach, required with the advent of COVID-19 using technology and being innovative in their support of our patients and carers. This is a fantastic opportunity for both individuals looking to gain experience at a Band 6 level, as well as those with existing experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Laura McCarthy Community Team Manager&lt;/p&gt;
